returns._0: a list of integer values, from 0 to upper-1

params.data: the list of values to order

returns._0: the ordered values with the corresponding ordered indices base implementation provided by https://gist.github.com/subhodi/b3b86cc13ad2636420963e692a4d896f

ceil(uint256).notice: returns the smallest integer value that is bigger than or equal to a number, using scaling by C

floor(uint256).notice: returns the largest integer value that is less than or equal to a number, using scaling by C

range(uint256).notice: produces a range of n values, from 0 to n-1

round(uint256).notice: returns the nearest integer to a number, using scaling by C

sort(uint256[]).notice: sorts a list of values in ascending order
